8:<I recently became a Math teacher.  I trained as a World Languages Teacher (German and French) and then retrained as an Elementary Literacy Specialist in the US.  Only three years ago did the opportunity arise for me to teach Math in First Grade at a school where students have a dedicated Math teacher all the way pre-K through 5.  I always loved Math and so jumped at the chance, but since taking the job I have been astounded at people's reactions to me as a "Math teacher".  You can see the fear in their eyes as I tell them what I do.  It is as if I have become a different breed of person.  Because I teach Math.  Some of my close friends have opened up about their own traumatic experiences in Math class and yes, those memories run deep.  Even I remember the year that I sat in 5th form Maths (UK) and just could not understand longitude and latitude to save my life.  

So one of my main goals as a first grade Math teacher (I would argue my most important goal) is to make sure that ALL of my students like Math.  I make them work hard, but I also make sure that all of their learning and their risk-taking is done in a safe environment where we learn from our mistakes.  

And I am soooo enjoying teaching Math :)   And I am looking forward to understanding my subject matter so much better after this course.>
