83:<A lot of the negative ideas and feelings about math do come from hearing other adults and peers. Yes what the media displayed on tv shows and movies does play a factor, but I think their personal in the classroom is the main cause of the phobia. If students are ONLY pushed to memorized and to complete worksheets after worksheets and not taught or allowed to apply and extend what they know then they will not see the relevance of learning the classroom math and how it's important to everyday life math. I apologize for such a long sentence at the end. You get the gist, just a little passionate about math. :)>
