85:<Interesting point about procedural teaching. I'm a language teacher and this seems to me like an analogy to teaching grammar and vocab in isolation vs presenting it to  students in a context (the latter being the more 'modern' approach). 

I find that some learners like to have grammar structures explained to them, others prefer to 'intuit' the meaning of the grammatical forms from a text/video etc. When you say 'procedural', do you mean something analogous to the 'grammar only' approach, where there is nothing to stimulate the students who learn better by intuition and seeing how the concepts work in context?

Sorry if I've overloaded this with language-teaching buzzwords! I hope my question to you is relatively clear nonetheless. :)>
