88:<I came across the concept of Productive Failure in 2010 at a symposium where Manu Kapur [http://www.icce2010.upm.edu.my/slides/ICCE_2010_ManuKapur.pdf][1] presented this very interesting concept about designing lessons for failure in order to maximize exploration and discussion (a very brief summary - there's a bit more to it). read more here: [http://scholar.google.com.au/scholar?q=Productive+failure&hl=en&as_sdt=0&as_vis=1&oi=scholart&sa=X&ei=_R3nUfL0GOSwiQfThIG4Cw&ved=0CCwQgQMwAA][2]


  [1]: http://www.icce2010.upm.edu.my/slides/ICCE_2010_ManuKapur.pdf
  [2]: http://scholar.google.com.au/scholar?q=Productive%20failure&hl=en&as_sdt=0&as_vis=1&oi=scholart&sa=X&ei=_R3nUfL0GOSwiQfThIG4Cw&ved=0CCwQgQMwAA>
