213:<We are given negative maths images from media, I think, because we have all been taught, for the most part, in the same way for the last 100(?) years. Media (and in all areas of human communication you will find in regards to maths, for example: via tv, parents conversing with children, magazines, etc.) are saying these things because they instinctively need and want a change. We continually share the results of the previously unsuccessful era of maths learning, because that is all we know. It's time we get to know something different, and our words and attitudes can change and bring about positive reflection on maths. It's a difficult subject of discussion. Our feelings around how we have been all treated via the schooling system thus far (specifically around maths) are strong and are evidently coming out EVERYWHERE. One of the only places I personally don't find a lot of hatred towards loving maths ideas and questing to find answers, is via the on-line gaming community. :)>
