252:<The benefit of doing this with students is that they can see just how many different ways people have of counting/doing math. And that there's not one correct way. There's usually one correct answer, but how you get there is a creative process. I know I get stuck seeing things one way only, and it's so helpful to get ideas from other people... maybe someone uses a more efficient way, or a way that makes more sense than the way you've been thinking about it solely due to habit. Then you can 'steal' this new ideas/approaches and use them as your own! :)>
