292:<First of all the dot card in the video looks like "diamond plating" on the back running board of a fire engine.

Okay.  Dot cards give you a visual representation to work from and toward a visualization of the numbers you see.  Dot cards provide an exercise in seeing patterns. Reinforce open mindset.  You can see in many different ways.

Dot cards give my brain a chance to drive a bit backwards, sideways, and serpentine in counting and representing numbers.  Instead of going from a value in standard form to a picture, I am able to see a value in picture form moving toward a standard form representation.  Dot cards give the brain flexibility, plasticity and allow for creativity.

It is also fun to see and hear other "sightings."   Personal UFOs.  :)>
