305:<I teach middle schoolers so  #1- They are social beings! (as are all of our students, but middle schoolers even more so). They need/want to talk. Better to talk about my math challenges than their weekend plans. :)

#2- Talking helps everyone solidify their own thinking. I tell them if they can explain it first orally, it will help them clarify their thinking for the paper/pencil explanation (if required). 

#3- Hearing other ways to solve problems helps other students open up to new ideas, new methods, new relationships. I tell students the best moment for me is when I hear a student say, "Ohhhh!!! Now I get it!" and that only happens on days when we're discussing something. They never make that realization on test day! :)>
