487:<I have loved this course so far and am getting a lot of good information.  However, this is the first item I beg to differ on.  I encourage my students to use letters that better represent the item that they are using.  I make them write out what each variable stands for at the beginning of each problem.

The first time I tell them that they can choose "better" letters than 'x' and 'y', I can see the light bulb go on.  I have had very few problems with students using "first letter variables" and misunderstanding what they actually mean.

I would be interested in seeing the research that shows this is a bad thing.

Thanks for the course!!  Back to Daniel and his grandma now  :-)>
